      • getNominalInputSequences

        public int[] getNominalInputSequences()
        Queries processing sequence size in samples.
        This value gives an approximate value of how many input samples you'll need to feed into SoundTouch after initial buffering to get out a new batch of output samples.

        This value does not include initial buffering at beginning of a new processing stream, use getInitialLatencies() to get the initial buffering size.
        Returns:
        Processing sequence size in samples.
        See Also:
        getInitialLatencies()

      • getNominalOutputSequences

        public int[] getNominalOutputSequences()
        Queries nominal average processing output size in samples.
        This value tells an approximate value of how many output samples SoundTouch outputs once it does DSP processing run for a batch of input samples.
        Returns:
        Nominal average processing output size in samples.

      • getInitialLatencies

        public int[] getInitialLatencies()
        Queries initial processing latencies, i.e. approx. how many samples you'll need to enter to SoundTouch pipeline before you can expect to get first batch of ready output samples out.
        Returns:
        Initial processing latencies.
